  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). An uncertainty quantification campaign was conducted covering inlet flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity; parametric sweeps across the five operating points confirmed monotonic hemolysis trends and bounded prediction uncertainty within ±12% of the nominal RH index. These UQ activities are summarised in the validation results narrative below.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
